content:
Runs test coverage analysis and generates a detailed report at the end of the session. Shows which parts of the code are well-tested and which need more coverage.

```json
{
  "Stop": [
    {
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "echo 'ðŸ§ª TEST COVERAGE REPORT' && echo '========================' && if [ -f 'package.json' ] && grep -q 'jest\\|mocha\\|vitest' package.json 2>/dev/null; then npm test -- --coverage --silent 2>/dev/null || npm run test:coverage 2>/dev/null || echo 'Coverage command not configured'; if [ -d 'coverage' ]; then echo 'ðŸ“Š Coverage Summary:' && cat coverage/coverage-summary.json 2>/dev/null | grep -E '\"(lines|branches|functions|statements)\"' | head -8 || echo 'Summary not available'; echo 'ðŸ“ˆ Coverage report: file://$(pwd)/coverage/index.html'; fi; elif [ -f 'requirements.txt' ] || [ -f 'setup.py' ]; then pytest --cov=. --cov-report=term-missing 2>/dev/null || python -m coverage report 2>/dev/null || echo 'Python coverage not configured'; fi && echo '========================'"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
